PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)
Project Name: AuraMatch AI (Scent & Dupe Engine)
Target Launch: July 8, 2026

1. Executive Summary & MVP Scope
AuraMatch is an AI-powered fragrance recommendation engine. It translates human lifestyle inputs (e.g., "I need a summer perfume for the gym because I sweat") into semantic vector embeddings to match users with high-end fragrances and their affordable chemical equivalents (dupes).

What is IN SCOPE for the 7-Day MVP:

The Vibe Check (Context Search): A dynamic, natural-language text input or 3-step minimal questionnaire.

The Dupe Radar: A specific feature to input a luxury perfume and return 3 budget alternatives using our hybrid math score (Semantic Similarity + Price Divergence).

Vector Search Engine: PostgreSQL pgvector integration.

Dockerized Ecosystem: Complete containerization of UI, API, and DB.

What is OUT OF SCOPE (Do not attempt these yet):

User authentication / Login systems (too much time, adds no ML value).

Shopping cart or payment gateways.

Scraping data live (we rely on a pre-loaded Kaggle CSV seed).

2. Frontend Design Language: "Subtle & Brutalist Luxury"
To stand out, your UI must avoid looking like a standard Bootstrap template. We are selling fragrance, which is inherently high-end, subjective, and aesthetic. We will use a design system I call "Minimalist Apothecary."

Color Palette:

Background: #FAFAFA (Alabaster White) or #F4F4F0 (Bone). Do not use pure white.

Primary Text: #1A1A1A (Soft Black).

Accents: #8C8C8C (Muted Stone) and #D1D1C7 (Sage/Warm Grey).

Typography:

Headings: Playfair Display or Cinzel (gives that high-end Tom Ford / Le Labo editorial feel).

Body/UI: Inter or Geist (clean, modern, highly legible).

UI/UX Vibe (Tailwind CSS):

Massive whitespace. Let the text breathe.

No heavy drop shadows. Use subtle 1px borders (border-stone-200) instead of shadows for a flat, print-magazine aesthetic.

Interactions: Fade-ins (opacity-0 to opacity-100 via Framer Motion) when transitioning between questionnaire steps. No bouncy or aggressive animations.

The User Flow
Landing Page: A stark, elegant screen. Just a bold headline: "Find your signature. Or steal theirs." with two buttons: Match by Lifestyle or Find a Dupe.

The Input: A minimalist chat-like input or form that asks "Tell us about your environment and chemistry."

The Reveal: A loading state that says "Analyzing olfactory profiles...", followed by a clean grid of 3 recommended bottles with progress bars showing "Match Score" (e.g., 94%).

3. Backend Architecture: The Microservice Illusion
In a strict microservices architecture, the ML model, the API gateway, and the database would all be heavily distributed. Given the 7-day constraint, we will build a Modular Monolith disguised as a microservice ecosystem inside Docker.

FastAPI is perfect for this. It is highly decoupled.

Repository Structure (Strict Separation of Concerns)
Plaintext
backend/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py                 # The FastAPI application & router gateway
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── dependencies.py     # DB connection pooling (asyncpg)
│   │   ├── routes_search.py    # Endpoint: Natural language context search
│   │   └── routes_dupe.py      # Endpoint: Luxury dupe finder
│   ├── core/
│   │   ├── config.py           # Environment variables (Pydantic BaseSettings)
│   │   └── security.py         # Rate limiting (if implemented)
│   ├── models/
│   │   └── schemas.py          # Pydantic models for request/response validation
│   └── services/
│       ├── ml_engine.py        # SentenceTransformer Singleton (Loaded once into RAM)
│       └── db_repository.py    # The raw SQL vector queries
├── Dockerfile                  
└── requirements.txt            
Core API Endpoints
POST /api/v1/search/context

Payload: {"query": "summer gym sweat aquatic", "budget": 50}

Returns: Top 3 items based purely on vector distance.

POST /api/v1/search/dupe

Payload: {"target_fragrance_id": 102, "max_price_ratio": 0.5}

Returns: High vector similarity, but strictly lower price.

GET /api/v1/health

Returns: {"status": "ok", "db_connected": true} (Crucial for Docker healthchecks).

4. Dockerization & Deployment Strategy
The evaluators want to run docker compose up and have the entire system work instantly.

The Network Topology
We define a custom bridge network called scent_net.

The DB Container (pgvector): Bootstraps first. Runs an init.sql script to create the schema and vector indexes.

The Backend Container (fastapi): Waits for the DB to be healthy. Crucial: We must bake the HuggingFace SentenceTransformer model directly into the Docker image during the docker build phase. Do not make the container download the 1GB model every time it boots, or the evaluator's demo will time out and fail.

The Frontend Container (react-nginx): A multi-stage build. Stage 1 compiles the Vite/React app. Stage 2 serves the static files using a lightweight Nginx image. Nginx acts as a reverse proxy, routing /api calls directly to the backend container, bypassing CORS issues.